<task id="t_psdk_ref_dvr-custom-start-point"> 
  <title>Choosing a custom starting point for DVR</title> 
  <shortdesc>You can choose a custom starting point for when to enter a DVR
	 stream instead of the default behavior of entering the DVR stream at the
	 beginning using the 
	 <apiname>ConfigProvider</apiname> class. 
  </shortdesc> 
  <taskbody> 
	 <context id="context_DC433D0A468E450881541AD53DB4E224"> 
		<p>To set the start time through the <xref
					href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/reference_implementation/android/javadoc/com/adobe/primetime/reference/config/ConfigProvider.html"
					format="html" scope="external">ConfigProvider</xref> class: </p> 
	 </context> 
	 <steps id="steps_4D42CD4411604D219C3EA2649268A4F4"> 
		<step id="step_01F8D6145A8D464FA31696540D9396F2">
				<cmd>Enable <xref
						href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/reference_implementation/android/javadoc/com/adobe/primetime/reference/config/ConfigProvider.html#isCustomPositionPrefEnabled()"
						format="html" scope="external">isCustomPositionPrefEnabled()</xref>. </cmd>
			</step> 
		<step id="step_99F915D4922C4F87A2C1C3858C3E9530">
				<cmd>Set the start time in <codeph><xref
							href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/reference_implementation/android/javadoc/com/adobe/primetime/reference/config/IPlaybackConfig.html#iretrieveStartTimePref()"
							format="html" scope="external">retrieveStartTimePref()</xref>.</codeph>
				</cmd>
			</step> 
		<step id="step_99925535FC2448C58308EB8EF3F447AB"> 
		  <cmd>Check that the custom start position is enabled. 
		  </cmd> 
		</step> 
	 </steps> 
  </taskbody> 
</task> 
